        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2012-10-18 07:52:21.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-2177 ptlrpc: flock/posix lock cause LBUGs because of a race",
        "message": "LU-2177 ptlrpc: flock/posix lock cause LBUGs because of a race\n\nThe below races can happen when some threads are handling flock or\nposix-lock\n\n1) LBUG in ldlm_lock_decref_internal_nolock()\nWhen a thread has granted ldlm_lock as PW mode and has finished ldlm\n_lock_enqueue() but hasn't called ldlm_flock_completion_ast() yet, a\nn evict process can set specific flags to the ldlm_lock of flock to\ncall ldlm_lock_decref_internal() in ldlm_flock_completion_ast().\nThis race causes calling ldlm_lock_decref_internal() in ldlm_flock_co\nmpletion_ast() twice or multiple times but unnecessarily.\n\n2) LBUG in ldlm_lock_destroy()\nWhen ldlm_flock_completion_ast() has already passed the if-statement\nto check LDLM_FL_FAILED but hasn't gotten lock_res_and_lock yet, an\nevict process can set LDLM_FL_FAILED flag to the ldlm_lock of flock\nwhich is being handled by this ldlm_flock_completion_ast().\nRight after this, if ldlm_flock_destroy() is called from the inside\nof ldlm_process_flock_lock(), it caused LBUG because no one can cal\nl ldlm_lock_decref_internal() to decrease l_writers due to lock_res\n_and_lock().\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: If928e18b3030a2eeb8c2d3341be6917e7561359b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
